<script>
  let activeTab = 'overview';

  function setTab(tab) {
    activeTab = tab;
  }
</script>

<template>
  <div class="shell">
    <aside class="sidebar">
      <div class="brand">FluxDOM <span>0.1</span></div>
      <p class="status">Experimental compiler-first UI framework.</p>
      <nav aria-label="Documentation sections">
        <button :class="activeTab === 'overview' ? 'active' : ''" @click="() => setTab('overview')">Overview</button>
        <button :class="activeTab === 'syntax' ? 'active' : ''" @click="() => setTab('syntax')">Supported syntax</button>
        <button :class="activeTab === 'limits' ? 'active' : ''" @click="() => setTab('limits')">Limitations</button>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <main class="content">
      {#if activeTab === 'overview'}
        <p class="eyebrow">Compiler first · direct DOM · fine-grained signals</p>
        <h1>A small laboratory for frontend framework ideas.</h1>
        <p class="lede">FluxDOM turns <strong>.flow</strong> components into explicit DOM operations. It is honest prototype code: useful for exploring compiler and runtime boundaries, not yet a production dependency.</p>
        <div class="grid">
          <section><h2>Parser</h2><p>Validated element nesting, expressions, reactive bindings, and nested control blocks.</p></section>
          <section><h2>Runtime</h2><p>Signals, computed state, effect cleanup, nested batching, and direct DOM helpers.</p></section>
          <section><h2>Tooling</h2><p>A Vite transform, virtual scoped CSS, a real project scaffold, and static-safe SSR.</p></section>
        </div>
      {/if}

      {#if activeTab === 'syntax'}
        <p class="eyebrow">Implemented today</p>
        <h1>The deliberately small `.flow` subset.</h1>
        <div class="code"><span>{`<button :class="active ? 'on' : ''" @click="increment">`}</span><span>{'  Count: {count}'}</span><span>{'</button>'}</span><span>{'{#each items as item, index} ... {/each}'}</span></div>
        <p class="lede">Nested <strong>if</strong> and <strong>each</strong> blocks compile, but loops rerender their whole block and conditionals use a display wrapper.</p>
      {/if}

      {#if activeTab === 'limits'}
        <p class="eyebrow">Production honesty</p>
        <h1>What FluxDOM does not promise yet.</h1>
        <div class="notice"><strong>Do not execute untrusted source.</strong> The script transform is a constrained prototype, hydration rerenders destructively, lifecycle hooks are placeholders, and full dynamic SSR is intentionally unavailable.</div>
        <p class="lede">The safe SSR path serializes static templates without eval. Dynamic components receive a client-rendering mount point.</p>
      {/if}
    </main>
  </div>
</template>

